Welcome to  Node.js study repository!

In this repository, you will find code snippets, examples, and projects related to my learning journey with Node.js.

To get started, make sure you have Node.js installed on your computer. You can download the latest version of Node.js from the official website (https://nodejs.org/en/).

The code in this repository covers the basics of Node.js, including setting up a development environment, creating a simple HTTP server, working with packages, and more advanced topics such as using Express.js, connecting to databases, and deploying your application to the cloud.